M|references|Detailed implementation guide for Google anl 4.
M|references|- cfg (data streams, enhanced measurement events, recommended events)
M|references|- Custom Events (gtag.js implementation, Google Tag Manager)
M|references|- Conversions Setup (creating conversions, conversion values)
M|references|- Custom Dimensions and Metrics (when to use, setup steps, examples)
M|references|- Audiences (creating audiences, audience examples)
M|references|- Debugging (DebugView, real-time reports, common issues)
M|references|- Data Quality (filters, cross-domain tracking, ses settings)
M|references|- Integration with Google Ads (linking, audience export)
M|references|- One stream per platform (web, iOS, Android)
M|references|- Enable enhanced measurement for automatic tracking
M|references|- Configure data retention (2 months default, 14 months max)
M|references|- Enable Google Signals (for cross-device, if consented)
M|references|| Event | Description | cfg |
M|references||-------|-------------|---------------|
M|references|| page_view | Page loads | Automatic |
M|references|| scroll | 90% scroll depth | Toggle on/off |
M|references|| outbound_click | Click to external domain | Automatic |
M|references|| site_search | Search query used | Configure parameter |
M|references|| video_engagement | YouTube video plays | Toggle on/off |
M|references|| file_download | PDF, docs, etc. | Configurable extensions |
M|references|Use Google's predefined events when possible for enhanced reporting:
M|references|**All properties:**
M|references|- login, sign_up
M|references|- share
M|references|- search
M|references|**E-commerce:**
M|references|- view_item, view_item_list
M|references|- add_to_cart, remove_from_cart
M|references|- begin_checkout
M|references|- add_payment_info
M|references|- purchase, refund
M|references|**Games:**
M|references|- level_up, unlock_achievement
M|references|- post_score, spend_virtual_currency
M|references|Reference: https://support.google.com/anl/answer/9267735
M|references|```javascript
M|references|// Basic event
M|references|gtag('event', 'signup_completed', {
M|references|'method': 'email',
M|references|'plan': 'free'
M|references|});
M|references|// Event with value
M|references|gtag('event', 'purchase', {
M|references|'transaction_id': 'T12345',
M|references|'value': 99.99,
M|references|'currency': 'USD',
M|references|'items': [{
M|references|'item_id': 'SKU123',
M|references|'item_name': 'Product Name',
M|references|'price': 99.99
M|references|}]
M|references|});
M|references|// User properties
M|references|gtag('set', 'user_properties', {
M|references|'user_type': 'premium',
M|references|'plan_name': 'pro'
M|references|});
M|references|// User ID (for logged-in users)
M|references|gtag('config', 'GA_MEASUREMENT_ID', {
M|references|'user_id': 'USER_ID'
M|references|});
M|references|```
M|references|```javascript
M|references|// Custom event
M|references|dataLayer.push({
M|references|'event': 'signup_completed',
M|references|'method': 'email',
M|references|'plan': 'free'
M|references|});
M|references|// Set user properties
M|references|dataLayer.push({
M|references|'user_id': '12345',
M|references|'user_type': 'premium'
M|references|});
M|references|// E-commerce purchase
M|references|dataLayer.push({
M|references|'event': 'purchase',
M|references|'ecommerce': {
M|references|'transaction_id': 'T12345',
M|references|'value': 99.99,
M|references|'currency': 'USD',
M|references|'items': [{
M|references|'item_id': 'SKU123',
M|references|'item_name': 'Product Name',
M|references|'price': 99.99,
M|references|'quantity': 1
M|references|}]
M|references|}
M|references|});
M|references|// Clear ecommerce before sending (best practice)
M|references|dataLayer.push({ ecommerce: null });
M|references|dataLayer.push({
M|references|'event': 'view_item',
M|references|'ecommerce': {
M|references|// ...
M|references|}
M|references|});
M|references|```
M|references|1. **Collect the event** - Ensure event is firing in GA4
M|references|2. **Mark as conversion** - Admin > Events > Mark as conversion
M|references|3. **Set counting method**:
M|references|- Once per ses (leads, signups)
M|references|- Every event (purchases)
M|references|4. **Import to Google Ads** - For conversion-optimized bidding
M|references|```javascript
M|references|// Event with conversion value
M|references|gtag('event', 'purchase', {
M|references|'value': 99.99,
M|references|'currency': 'USD'
M|references|});
M|references|```
M|references|Or set default value in GA4 Admin when marking conversion.
M|references|**Custom dimensions:**
M|references|- Properties you want to segment/filter by
M|references|- User attributes (plan type, industry)
M|references|- cnt attributes (author, category)
M|references|**Custom metrics:**
M|references|- Numeric values to aggregate
M|references|- Scores, counts, durations
M|references|1. Admin > Data display > Custom definitions
M|references|2. Create dimension or metric
M|references|3. Choose scope:
M|references|- **Event**: Per event (content_type)
M|references|- **User**: Per user (account_type)
M|references|- **Item**: Per product (product_category)
M|references|4. Enter parameter name (must match event parameter)
M|references|| Dimension | Scope | Parameter | Description |
M|references||-----------|-------|-----------|-------------|
M|references|| User Type | User | user_type | Free, trial, paid |
M|references|| cnt Author | Event | author | Blog post author |
M|references|| Product Category | Item | item_category | E-commerce category |
M|references|Admin > Data display > Audiences
M|references|**Use cases:**
M|references|- Remarketing audiences (export to Ads)
M|references|- Segment analysis
M|references|- Trigger-based events
M|references|**High-intent visitors:**
M|references|- Viewed pricing page
M|references|- Did not convert
M|references|- In last 7 days
M|references|**Engaged users:**
M|references|- 3+ sessions
M|references|- Or 5+ minutes total engagement
M|references|**Purchasers:**
M|references|- Purchase event
M|references|- For exclusion or lookalike
M|references|Enable with:
M|references|- URL parameter: `?debug_mode=true`
M|references|- Chrome extension: GA Debugger
M|references|- gtag: `'debug_mode': true` in config
M|references|View at: Reports > Configure > DebugView
M|references|Check events within 30 minutes:
M|references|Reports > Real-time
M|references|**Events not appearing:**
M|references|- Check DebugView first
M|references|- Verify gtag/GTM firing
M|references|- Check filter exclusions
M|references|**Parameter values missing:**
M|references|- Custom dimension not created
M|references|- Parameter name mismatch
M|references|- Data still processing (24-48 hrs)
M|references|**Conversions not recording:**
M|references|- Event not marked as conversion
M|references|- Event name doesn't match
M|references|- Counting method (once vs. every)
M|references|Admin > Data streams > [Stream] > Configure tag settings > Define internal traffic
M|references|**Exclude:**
M|references|- Internal IP addresses
M|references|- Developer traffic
M|references|- Testing environments
M|references|For multiple domains sharing anl:
M|references|1. Admin > Data streams > [Stream] > Configure tag settings
M|references|2. Configure your domains
M|references|3. List all domains that should share sessions
M|references|Admin > Data streams > [Stream] > Configure tag settings
M|references|- ses timeout (default 30 min)
M|references|- Engaged ses duration (10 sec default)
M|references|1. Admin > Product links > Google Ads links
M|references|2. Enable auto-tagging in Google Ads
M|references|3. Import conversions in Google Ads
M|references|Audiences created in GA4 can be used in Google Ads for:
M|references|- Remarketing cg
M|references|- Customer match
M|references|- Similar audiences